---
import ProjectDetail from '../../layouts/ProjectDetail.astro';
---

<ProjectDetail
  title="Friend Finder"
  description="A fully local, self-hosted RAG chat widget that answers questions about a website's content — no external APIs, embedded on a WordPress site to help reconnect old friends."
  tags={['RAG', 'Ollama', 'ChromaDB', 'FastAPI']}
  github="https://github.com/MariamKhubashvilii/Friends-Reconnected-Chatbot"
  accent="pink"
  comingSoon={true}
>
  <section class="project-grid">
    <article class="project-card summary-card">
      <h2>Project summary</h2>
      <p>
        Friend Finder is a fully local, self-hosted chatbot that answers questions about website content without relying on external APIs. It combines web scraping, vector embeddings, and a local language model into a privacy-first, cost-effective solution — deployed as a widget on the Friends Reconnected WordPress site.
      </p>
      <div class="summary-list">
        <div>
          <strong>Fully local</strong>
          <p>No cloud dependencies or API fees — scraping, embeddings, and the LLM all run on your own machine.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Smart updates</strong>
          <p>MD5 fingerprints detect what changed, so new pages can be added without re-embedding the whole database.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card detail-card">
      <h2>What this project shows</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>JavaScript-aware scraping with Playwright and BeautifulSoup.</li>
        <li>Incremental indexing with content-change detection.</li>
        <li>Streaming token responses over Server-Sent Events.</li>
        <li>WordPress integration as an embeddable iframe widget.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section">
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        The system runs in three stages: Playwright scrapes JavaScript-rendered pages and BeautifulSoup extracts clean text; sentence-transformers convert text chunks into embeddings stored in ChromaDB; and incoming questions are embedded, matched against stored vectors, and answered by a local Ollama model with streaming responses.
      </p>

      <div class="section-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>Pipeline</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Scrape via explicit URLs, sitemaps, or recursive crawl</li>
            <li>Chunk and embed with all-MiniLM-L6-v2</li>
            <li>Store vectors in persistent local ChromaDB</li>
            <li>Answer with Ollama (Llama 3.2 / Mistral), streamed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Tech stack</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Scraping: Playwright + BeautifulSoup</li>
            <li>Embeddings: sentence-transformers</li>
            <li>Backend: FastAPI with Server-Sent Events</li>
            <li>Frontend: vanilla HTML/JavaScript widget</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section project-usage">
    <h2>Run it</h2>
    <p>
      Install Ollama and pull a model (<code>ollama pull llama3.2</code>), then set up the Python environment. Scrape content with <code>python scrape.py --urls &lt;URLs&gt;</code> (or <code>--sitemap</code> / <code>--crawl</code>), build embeddings with <code>python ingest.py</code>, and launch with <code>uvicorn app:app --reload --port 8000</code>. Add new pages later with <code>--update</code> and the system skips unchanged content.
    </p>
    <div class="usage-card">
      <div>
        <strong>Live</strong>
        <p><a href="https://friendsreconnected.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">friendsreconnected.co.uk</a></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Best for</strong>
        <p>Site owners who want a private, no-API chatbot over their own content.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectDetail>
